<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80c1f9a7-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s6132"><num value="6132">§ 6132.</num><heading> Sale of articles, signs, and solicitation in Supreme Court Building and grounds</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">It is unlawful—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id80c1f9a8-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s6132/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> to offer or expose any article for sale in the Supreme Court Building or grounds;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id80c1f9a9-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s6132/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> to display a sign, placard, or other form of advertisement in the Building or grounds; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id80c1f9aa-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s6132/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> to solicit fares, alms, subscriptions, or contributions in the Building or grounds.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id80c1f9ab-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1183">116 Stat. 1183</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
